Welcome to Police Chase In Progress! 

We offer impartial and genuine footage from body cameras capturing various incidents. Our aim is to present this footage as an educational resource for our audience.

All the content on our channel is original and exclusive, not previously featured on YouTube.

The raw footage used in our videos is sourced directly from Police Departments. Obtaining this footage typically involves a fee (averaging $500 per case) and processing time of several days. It's important to note that our channel operates independently of any law enforcement agency.

We adhere to YouTube's Fair Use Policy by crafting narratives and condensing lengthy footage into concise, educational, and engaging videos. 

The content showcased is not intended to shame, ridicule, or demean individuals involved, nor does it aim to glorify violence in any manner.

Sincerely,
~Police Chase In Progress Team~

- The crashes shown in my videos are NOT from any public games.

- Most of these crashes use real audio, but the ROBLOX crashes themselves are not recreations of the original crashes (except for the Cars vs. Trains series) Some crashes use BeamNG audio.

description:
My name is NICOLAS, when I’m thinking about my life and when I see the world, I’m feeling nostalgic. Even if I’m part of what they call generation Z, I miss the world of my parents. Relationships have changed, the world has changed, love has changed and people forget to feel. I’m thankful for internet’s ability to remind me of my friends' birthday, to put my music online in few minutes, to remind me where I was last year on the same day and to have a better memory than I really have but internet isn't able to remind me how I felt today, when I released my first project or when I met you.

I’m still figuring out a way to find who I am and what my life will be and I’m using music to express my feelings and internet to have a record of who I am. If you want to remember, be part of my, your, our project.

description:
主に東北・東日本、時には日本全国？を走る列車や車窓を中心に撮影しています。
新幹線の迫力やバリエーションに富んだ列車、または車窓を紹介しています。

生粋の宮城人。東北の鉄道の良さを通じ、震災からの復興の力となれば良いな
と思ったのがYouTube動画投稿のきっかけ。
幼少の頃、まだ東北新幹線が開業していない国鉄時代からの鉄道ファン。
多くの鉄道ファンと違い、田んぼの多い田舎出身で休日は、春～夏は草刈り、庭の手入れ
また地元自治会の役員の仕事等もしながら隙間を見つけては
撮影と編集作業に1名で勤しんでいます！

動画にはあまり細かい説明は載せない方針ですが
YouTubeの字幕機能で簡単な解説、または独り言？を
つぶやいている事も。

Hey, I'm just a guy who loves experimenting with the BeamNG.drive physics.

Have you ever wondered what will happen to a car, truck or bus when they try to pass through a pothole or massive speed bump or flooded road at different speeds? The game allows you to experiment with all of those and I can tell you that the simulations in the game are pretty realistic.

All videos on this channel are created and edited only by me.

How I make my YouTube videos:
- at first I prepare everything in game, making scenes for recording.
- after everything is prepared, I use Xbox Game Bar to record the scenes.
- then I use editing programs: Adobe Premiere Pro (to create and render a video) and Photoshop (to create a thumbnail).
- and the final step is when I upload the rendered video to YouTube.

My PC Specs:
CPU: Intel Core i7-4790K @ 4.00GHz

CityNerd is a channel and community that embraces all things cities and transportation, approaching things with a profound love for urban environments and an analytical bent. Every aspect of CityNerd is currently produced by yours truly (Ray Delahanty). Research, writing, on-camera "talent" (cough cough), editing, engaging with viewers....yeah, it's all me. I'll update this description just as soon as I hire a crack team of researchers and cinematographers.

description:
Welcome to CRASHHub! My mission is to entertain you guys with an awesome channel that celebrates the fun in crash physics, with a whole host of different themed videos.

I spend 70-80 hours per week making these videos. It takes about 12 hours on average to make a video - every single scenes is set up by hand by me, the camera angles, focus depth, focus length, simulation speed and lighting all adjusted by me, then it's recorded, 35GB of footage is edited, painstakingly synchronized to music and sound effects added by hand. 

Videos about:
- Endurance testing of vehicles - Will they still drive after a whole host of different kinds of endurance and crash tests?
- How far will they go? - Seeing how far vehicles will travel over / under / through obstacles at max speed.
- Police chases videos - Action packed videos with planes, tanks, jets, rockets and even exploding robot chickens featured.
- And many, many other series' featured on this channel

I hope you enjoy the wild ride!!

Answers to some common questions:

1. I learned almost everything by building models as a kid.
2. I don’t have an engineering degree, as in school I found maths quite difficult. Everything is self-taught!
3. My first RC plane was a Super Cub, which I still have to this day. 
4. I drive a Mini.
5. The other people who help make these videos are Emma (who assists with building all sorts of things), Hannah (who films the big tests), and other friends who enjoy helping out from time-to-time.
6. My #1 top tip for getting into this stuff is to build model kits!

Hello, I'm Andy. My goal is to create entertaining videos mostly, but not only, for people who love cars & crashes. 

All the videos you'll find in this channel are recorded & edited by me and my sidekick, George, who helps with parts of the editing.
This channel is our full-time job. We're devoting a minimum of 100 hours per week to bring you the best BeamNG drive videos.

How we work:

Creating these videos is a lot harder & time consuming than you might think but it is what makes us and, hopefully, you happy!
We are playing BeamNG.drive, a PC Game featuring the ultimate soft-body physics and realism. 

The process, step by step:

- Recording the clips with Action! (10-15 hours, sometimes 15+)
- Editing & synchronizing the clips with music & addition of captions / sound effects - Premiere Pro (5-10 hours)  
- Descriptions, Thumbnails etc.  (2 hours)

We’re uploading 4 Videos per week on Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday & Sunday. Stay up to date by Subscribing!
Thank you :)

 hoy en día conocido como EL GATO - GATfilms
desde los 16 años he sido bailarín de break dance y mucho más género de la cultura latina.

Mi carrera incluye haber sido bailarín de Arcangel, telonero de Wisin y Yandel, talento creativo de películas de Son de la Calle.

llegué a Israel en el año 2010 Tras pasar la barrera del idioma y las complicaciones migratorias a causa de la ruptura de relaciones entre Venezuela e Israel que sucedió en el 2009, comencé otro trecho de mi vida exitosa en mi carrera artística vinculada al baile, con participación en shows, festivales, películas  y comerciales, para luego pasar desde el 2014 a la filmación, edición y producción de videos a famosos cantantes de Israel con giras incluidas a Francia, Estados Unidos, Chipre, Rusia, España y más recientemente a la música

ahora en tiempos post pandemia he decidido iniciar mi camino como cantante con el género de la bachata…

description:
Welcome to TK's Plane Spotting. I have been plane spotting for a number of years now and decided to turn it into a shared passion with this channel. This channel has been designed to highlight and promote the hobby of Plane Spotting. Over the last few years I've spent considerable amounts to time filming at Melbourne and Sydney Airports and bringing to you stunning 4K videos of the experiences had. Each video is designed to showcase something unique to aircraft and link my passion of being outdoors at the same time. I hope you find the same enjoyment in these videos as much as I enjoy filming and editing them for you all to enjoy! 

What is the purpose of this channel?
This channel has been established to share a passion for aviation and plane spotting. The community is a broad one stretching all over the globe. Showcasing what's on offer in Australian aviation is my contribution.

What to expect?
Clear 4K stunning footage, check it out for yourself! 

Cheers
TK

We know you're all fab, but here are some short house rules:

• Please be respectful of each other and of our record holders.
• We will always welcome new applications - if you think you can break a record, please do apply. 
• Spam posts will result in an instant ban.
• If you have a question about an application or a customer services issue you'd like to raise with the team, please head to www.guinnessworldrecords.com/contact to send a message.

Joseph Akinwale Akinfenwa-Donus (Born May 21, 1997) is an Afropop singer who hails from Ogun state, Nigeria. As the last born in a family of 4, Joeboy grew up a shy and timid kid who was raised
in a religiously inclined household. Through the influences of his musically inclined
parents and older brother as well as the unique sounds of the Nigerian church,Joeboy absorbed the cocktail of sonics and unwittingly tapped into the musicality surrounding him.

At the age of 18, Joeboy started actively working on his music, albeit privately, till he
gathered courage to actively put himself out there which was when his cover of Ed Sheeran’s Shape of you caught the attention of Superstar Mr. Eazi.

Often referred to as “Young Legend”,
Joeboy has over 60 songs (features included) with 2 albums (Somewhere Between Beauty & Magic and Body & Soul) and 2 EPs (Love & Light and Body, Soul & Spirit) to his name including Alcohol which has over 100 million views on YouTube.

Eric Hall showcases his model train layout progress, offering a unique perspective on Model Trains, Model Railroad Operations, and scale model trains. The channel features instructional videos, from train operations to model train accessories.

Explore the nuances of Model Trains, Model Railroad, and layout building at IMRROcom. Join the community, subscribe at https://www.youtube.com/@IMRROcom?sub_confirmation=1, and share the passion for trains and model railroad adventures. Happy railroading!

Hello and welcome to BeamNG Creation YouTube channel!  BeamNG drive is my passion and I love playing this game. My mission is to present top quality and of highest standard editing BeamNG drive videos with unique, meaningful and fun content.
 
BeamNG drive is the most realistic driving game that mimics every component of a vehicle in real time resulting in life like behavior.

I spend 40-45 hours weekly to make these videos. It takes 4 to 5 hours to setup, create a scene and record video clips with different camera angles. I then spend 2-3 hours editing these clips to a single completed video before uploading to YouTube.  All steps like vehicle control, camera angles, field of vision are done by myself.  

Videos about:
-Endurance testing of vehicles for crash tests?
-How far will they go over/under/through obstacles at max speed?
-How well they can handle a crash?
-And many many other series featured on this channel

 Join us and be part of this adventure.

Playing music should be fun! On this channel I write songs out for you in Letter Note Style so that you can have fun playing songs! I do most of this by ear & try to do trending songs & sounds. When I was a kid my baby brother had cancer. My family was too busy taking him to the hospital to take me to piano lessons. Hello and welcome to the Energy crash YouTube channel! As you'll see, I have a passion for storytelling and experimenting using the BeamNG.drive physics simulation sandbox. This channel exists as a platform for me to share my stories, experiments and other mayhem created in BeamNG.drive.

I create my videos by first recording many hours of my own unique and custom scenarios within BeamNG.drive using OBS Studio. I then spend a significant amount of time editing these clips in Davinci Resolve to create a story before finally uploading the completed video to YouTube. This is a long process and while I strive to upload videos on a consistent basis, I typically average a few uploads per week.
